Date of Birth: September 2, 1906<br/>
Birthplace: Oakley, Idaho, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: January 8, 1976<br/>
Death: July 31, 2004<br/>
<br/>
Born Sept. 2, 1906, in Oakley, Idaho, to Hector C. Haight and Clara Tuttle. Sustained as Assistant to the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles April 6, 1970, at age 63; ordained apostle Jan 8, 1976, by Spencer W. Kimball, at age 69; sustained to the Quorum of the Twelve April 3, 1976; died July 31, 2004, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 97.